Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri The Deputy Governor of Imo State, Mr Gerald Irona, has denied slapping the lawmaker representing Ikeduru state constituency in the House of Assembly, Uche Ogbuagu. Irona was alleged to have slapped Ogbuagu during a meeting at the Government House in Owerri. However, in a statement by his media aide, Walter Duru, the deputy governor said there was no truth in the rumour. The statement said that the rumour was peddled to paint the deputy governor in a bad image. He accused the members of the opposition of being behind the rumour, adding that the deputy governor had no trait of violence in him. The statement said, â€œOur attention has been drawn to a report trending on social media, alleging that the Deputy Governor of Imo State, Gerald Irona, slapped a lawmaker in Imo State. Copyright PUNCH.
